The Do's:


Do use strong, unique passwords for every social platform.


Do enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) for extra security.


Do keep your professional profiles (like LinkedIn) updated with current skills.


Do review your privacy settings regularly to control who sees your posts.


Do think twice before posting content that could impact your future career.







The Don'ts:


Don't share your location, ID, or personal schedule publicly.


Don't post controversial or offensive content that could hurt your reputation.


Don't accept friend requests from complete strangers or suspicious accounts.


Don't click on shortened links in direct messages from unknown users.


Don't use your college email password for your social media accounts
